WEBVTT

1
00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:03.640
There's somebody down there.

2
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:06.639
Is he gone yet? Is he gone?

3
00:01:07.679 --> 00:01:10.080
-Sir. he's gone.
-Okay. let's go.

4
00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:16.480
Anybody home?

5
00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:19.880
Idiot.

6
00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:29.760
Close the door.

7
00:01:32.800 --> 00:01:36.640
-You know what to look for. right?
-Yeah. No. A light switch?

8
00:01:37.801 --> 00:01:40.282
Please try not to be such an idiot.

9
00:01:51.081 --> 00:01:53.281
-I'm okay.
-Nobody asked.

10
00:02:11.881 --> 00:02:14.321
-He's not here.
-Who?

11
00:02:15.081 --> 00:02:18.441
-Commissioner Hurst.
-Of course he's not here.

12
00:02:19.882 --> 00:02:23.401
It's 3:00 in the morning. That's the point.

13
00:02:24.841 --> 00:02:26.561
Maybe we should have called first.

14
00:02:27.401 --> 00:02:30.763
If I'd wanted the Commissioner
to watch me while I looked at his files...

15
00:02:30.843 --> 00:02:33.842
I could have come in during the day
and made an appointment.

16
00:02:33.922 --> 00:02:38.321
Wait a minute. You mean
we're breaking and entering illegally?

17
00:02:38.802 --> 00:02:41.361
-We are breaking the Law?
-No.

18
00:02:41.562 --> 00:02:43.802
We are not breaking the Law.

19
00:02:43.882 --> 00:02:47.202
We are merely stretching it a little.

20
00:02:52.522 --> 00:02:55.402
It's okay to break the law
if you have a good reason...

21
00:02:55.482 --> 00:02:59.403
-like a note from your doctor or mom.
-We are not breaking the Law.

22
00:03:00.163 --> 00:03:02.843
We are stretching it.

23
00:03:04.002 --> 00:03:05.163
Do you get it?

24
00:03:07.363 --> 00:03:11.083
-Not really. sir.
-I got a note in my pocket. okay?

25
00:03:12.243 --> 00:03:14.643
Okay. Why didn't you just say that?

26
00:03:19.083 --> 00:03:21.003
Commissioner Hurst....

27
00:03:38.924 --> 00:03:40.844
"Comdt. Eric Lassard."

28
00:03:42.365 --> 00:03:45.044
Well. there he is.

29
00:03:45.844 --> 00:03:48.403
For years you've kept me
from my rightful place...

30
00:03:48.484 --> 00:03:50.523
as Commandant of the Police Academy.

31
00:03:50.603 --> 00:03:53.964
You always manage to come out on top
somehow. don't you?

32
00:04:06.725 --> 00:04:09.605
I know that there is
something in this file...

33
00:04:09.645 --> 00:04:13.085
that is going to help me
get the upper hand for a change.

34
00:04:22.604 --> 00:04:24.004
Who's in there?

35
00:04:25.644 --> 00:04:26.805
Commissioner Hurst?

36
00:04:27.324 --> 00:04:29.644
Yes. Who's out there?

37
00:04:31.245 --> 00:04:32.765
Bob the janitor. sir.

38
00:04:35.966 --> 00:04:39.205
I understand. sir.
And I didn't see you here tonight.

39
00:04:39.925 --> 00:04:44.284
-I really appreciate that. Bob.
-Yeah. Thanks a lot. Bob.

40
00:04:46.765 --> 00:04:48.165
-Proctor.
-Yes. sir?

41
00:04:48.206 --> 00:04:52.245
This is it! According to these records.
Comdt. Eric Lassard...

42
00:04:52.405 --> 00:04:56.925
reached the state's
mandatory retirement age Last year!

43
00:04:58.926 --> 00:05:02.006
-Don't you see what this means?
-No!

44
00:05:04.805 --> 00:05:07.045
This means that Comdt. Lassard...

45
00:05:07.086 --> 00:05:11.525
should have retired
from the Police Academy a year ago.

46
00:05:12.366 --> 00:05:15.286
Somehow. this information
just slipped through.

47
00:05:17.285 --> 00:05:20.485
I find it my duty
as a conscientious police officer...

48
00:05:20.526 --> 00:05:24.966
to see to it
that this file reaches the Personnel Office.

49
00:05:29.646 --> 00:05:32.566
Are we going to have to
break in there. too. sir?

50
00:05:38.086 --> 00:05:39.887
Officer Katherine Page.

51
00:05:43.086 --> 00:05:44.566
Thank you. sir.

52
00:05:46.487 --> 00:05:48.207
Officer Carla Grant.

53
00:05:53.608 --> 00:05:54.887
Thank you.

54
00:05:58.166 --> 00:05:59.807
Officer Bill Baker.

55
00:06:04.847 --> 00:06:06.286
Thank you. sir.

56
00:06:09.367 --> 00:06:11.168
Officer Bambi Brandon.

57
00:06:27.887 --> 00:06:30.247
-Thank you. sir.
-Thank you.

58
00:06:38.128 --> 00:06:40.168
Officer Kevin Wilson.

59
00:06:49.808 --> 00:06:53.768
And last. but certainly not least.
not in any way...

60
00:06:54.448 --> 00:06:56.248
Officer Thomas Conklin.

61
00:07:02.129 --> 00:07:03.609
Also known as House.

62
00:07:04.968 --> 00:07:06.529
Congratulations!

63
00:07:06.608 --> 00:07:10.849
I'll miss you. Class of '88.

64
00:07:22.848 --> 00:07:23.890
Nice.

65
00:07:28.009 --> 00:07:30.529
I've seen a lot of graduating classes.

66
00:07:31.209 --> 00:07:34.769
And let me say that
this is one of the very best of them.

67
00:07:35.569 --> 00:07:39.009
Clearly. Comdt. Lassard
has outdone himself this time.

68
00:07:39.808 --> 00:07:44.129
It's my privilege to announce
that Comdt. Eric Lassard...

69
00:07:44.209 --> 00:07:47.409
will be honored
as Police Officer of the Decade...

70
00:07:47.489 --> 00:07:49.930
at this year's
National Police Chiefs Convention...

71
00:07:50.010 --> 00:07:51.970
to be held in Miami Beach.

72
00:08:00.210 --> 00:08:02.930
This Academy owes a great debt...

73
00:08:02.970 --> 00:08:05.489
to the vision of Comdt. Lassard...

74
00:08:05.690 --> 00:08:09.210
which makes what I have to say next
even more difficult.

75
00:08:10.170 --> 00:08:12.690
It is with great sadness and regret...

76
00:08:13.251 --> 00:08:16.371
that I must announce
Eric Lassard's retirement...

77
00:08:16.371 --> 00:08:18.891
as Commandant of this police academy.

78
00:08:19.050 --> 00:08:23.290
Comdt. Lassard has reached
this state's mandatory retirement age.

79
00:08:23.491 --> 00:08:26.651
A gualified successor will.
of course. be chosen.

80
00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:32.090
But the new commandant
will have no easy task filling these shoes.

81
00:08:33.650 --> 00:08:36.371
-What are we going to do?
-Kick some butt.

82
00:08:38.492 --> 00:08:41.731
-It's just not right.
-This is so unfair.

83
00:08:42.851 --> 00:08:46.931
-I've never seen him like this.
-He was always so strong.

84
00:08:47.290 --> 00:08:50.292
-The Academy was his strength.
-Now he's lost it.

85
00:08:50.891 --> 00:08:52.571
It's just not right.

86
00:08:54.291 --> 00:08:57.491
-Why don't we just shoot somebody?
-Commandant.

87
00:08:59.851 --> 00:09:03.412
-No. He ain't worth it.
-Congratulations on your retirement!

88
00:09:03.572 --> 00:09:06.892
I'm sorry. I mean on your award
in Miami Beach.

89
00:09:07.212 --> 00:09:08.971
Concerning your retirement. sir...

90
00:09:09.012 --> 00:09:12.492
I want you to know how much I've enjoyed
working with you all these years...

91
00:09:12.612 --> 00:09:14.891
and how much I hope you enjoy...

92
00:09:14.931 --> 00:09:18.252
your long overdue rest.

93
00:09:19.092 --> 00:09:22.932
Well. I guess I'll run along
and read my book.

94
00:09:25.331 --> 00:09:27.252
Keep in touch. everyone.

95
00:09:40.412 --> 00:09:44.053
They just keep staring at each other.
We've got to do something.

96
00:09:46.373 --> 00:09:50.132
I know how you feel. sir.
I was ready to toss in the towel. too.

97
00:09:50.612 --> 00:09:54.613
Then I met a man who changed my life.
That man was you. sir.

98
00:09:56.012 --> 00:09:59.014
He said. "Take what you have.
however little...

99
00:09:59.093 --> 00:10:00.773
"and do your best with it."

100
00:10:01.493 --> 00:10:05.892
"Never quit. Never lose hope."
That's the lassard I knew.

101
00:10:06.133 --> 00:10:08.893
And where is that lassard now?

102
00:10:10.453 --> 00:10:11.453
Right here.

103
00:10:13.173 --> 00:10:14.893
By God. you're right.

104
00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:19.653
I was feeling sorry for myself. No more.

105
00:10:22.973 --> 00:10:24.894
I'm still being honored...

106
00:10:25.014 --> 00:10:28.374
at the National Police Chiefs Convention
in Miami Beach.

107
00:10:28.494 --> 00:10:32.413
-Affirmative. sir!
-Go there with my head held high.

108
00:10:32.533 --> 00:10:36.612
-Yes. sir!
-It will be my finest hour!

109
00:10:36.693 --> 00:10:38.214
-Duck!
-Get down!

110
00:10:38.734 --> 00:10:40.534
That's the spirit. sir.

111
00:10:42.014 --> 00:10:43.294
Good shot.

112
00:10:43.414 --> 00:10:46.174
It would make my crowning moment
only greater...

113
00:10:46.294 --> 00:10:48.814
if my loyal graduates could be there
to share it with me.

114
00:10:48.894 --> 00:10:51.614
Miami Beach? All that surf. sun. and fun?

115
00:10:51.695 --> 00:10:55.854
Then you can meet Nick. my nephew.
He's a policeman in Miami Beach.

116
00:10:56.014 --> 00:10:58.374
We'll do it. sir. But only for you.

117
00:11:01.173 --> 00:11:03.614
You have all given me new hope.

118
00:11:03.693 --> 00:11:05.935
-Way to go. sir.
-We're so proud of you.

119
00:11:05.975 --> 00:11:10.374
If I cannot stay. then I'll go out in style.

120
00:11:12.215 --> 00:11:15.255
Miami Beach. get ready.

121
00:11:16.534 --> 00:11:19.695
Get ready for Eric Lassard!

122
00:11:28.094 --> 00:11:29.294
The fish!

123
00:11:35.816 --> 00:11:38.056
It's good to have you back. sir.

124
00:11:51.255 --> 00:11:53.295
And I can assure you. this Academy...

125
00:11:53.415 --> 00:11:57.575
under my administration. will no longer
be a source of any embarrassment to you.

126
00:11:57.656 --> 00:12:01.217
-Yes. so you keep telling me.
-Sir.

127
00:12:01.656 --> 00:12:04.976
Clean office.
My office hasn't been cleaned in a week.

128
00:12:05.616 --> 00:12:08.695
-Janitor quit on me.
-Excuse me. sir.

129
00:12:08.736 --> 00:12:12.456
Commissioner. I would like you to look at
this plan that I have formulated.

130
00:12:12.536 --> 00:12:15.496
-It completely restructures--
-I don't mean to bother you. sir!

131
00:12:15.576 --> 00:12:16.856
...here at the Academy.

132
00:12:16.895 --> 00:12:19.697
Harris. you may Well be the best man
for this position.

133
00:12:19.737 --> 00:12:22.816
You may even wind up
as commandant of this Academy.

134
00:12:22.936 --> 00:12:26.977
But you sure have a lot to learn
about acting like a commandant.

135
00:12:29.536 --> 00:12:33.656
At least Lassard has the respect
of his men. Whose respect do you have?

136
00:12:36.376 --> 00:12:39.255
-Commissioner shouldn't have said that.
-He's right.

137
00:12:39.337 --> 00:12:41.296
I know. sir...

138
00:12:43.656 --> 00:12:46.778
but he still shouldn't say it.

139
00:12:47.897 --> 00:12:49.377
No. he's right.

140
00:12:50.417 --> 00:12:52.737
Being qualified just isn't enough.

141
00:12:52.857 --> 00:12:56.457
Now. I know that I was born
to be commandant.

142
00:12:56.537 --> 00:12:58.777
It is my destiny.

143
00:13:00.897 --> 00:13:05.137
You and I are going to Miami Beach.

144
00:13:05.977 --> 00:13:08.018
-We are?
-Don't you see?

145
00:13:08.298 --> 00:13:11.218
We'll go to Miami Beach
and help honor Lassard.

146
00:13:11.337 --> 00:13:14.738
That will show the Commissioner
what a big man I can be.

147
00:13:16.737 --> 00:13:19.418
-Yes. sir.
-Get on the phone. Call the airport.

148
00:13:19.457 --> 00:13:21.818
Make a reservation to Miami Beach.

149
00:13:21.858 --> 00:13:23.458
-First class.
-VIP.

150
00:13:23.538 --> 00:13:27.378
-VIP. I'll impress them from the start.
-That's brilliant. sir.

151
00:13:28.377 --> 00:13:30.297
Jones. pick up the phone.

152
00:13:32.057 --> 00:13:33.017
Up.

153
00:13:37.659 --> 00:13:39.258
When's Lassard coming back?

154
00:13:40.458 --> 00:13:42.179
I didn't know he was gone.

155
00:13:44.338 --> 00:13:47.219
Hello. municipal airport?
This is it. Proctor...

156
00:13:47.298 --> 00:13:50.698
of the Metropolitan Police Academy.
Capt. Harris will be attending...

157
00:13:50.778 --> 00:13:53.498
the NationaI Police Chiefs Convention
in Miami Beach...

158
00:13:53.538 --> 00:13:57.977
and will require two first class tickets
aboard your most prestigious flight.

159
00:13:58.098 --> 00:13:59.979
All lines are busy. Please hold.

160
00:14:01.819 --> 00:14:05.539
I got Proctor on the telephone trying to
book two first-class tickets to Miami...

161
00:14:05.619 --> 00:14:08.299
for him and Harris.
And he thinks I'm the airport.

162
00:14:08.339 --> 00:14:10.699
Great. Just what we need in Miami. Harris.

163
00:14:10.778 --> 00:14:11.978
No. wait.

164
00:14:12.938 --> 00:14:15.059
Put him on hold for a minute.

165
00:14:16.979 --> 00:14:20.099
Checking computers right now. sir.
Please stand by.

166
00:14:32.180 --> 00:14:35.339
I'd like the number
for Budget Rent a Plane. please.

167
00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:45.820
-Come on. pal. let's go.
-Yeah. Okay.

168
00:15:10.060 --> 00:15:11.060
Go!

169
00:15:13.781 --> 00:15:14.741
Go!

170
00:15:21.540 --> 00:15:23.381
-Here. boss.
-Here.

171
00:15:24.701 --> 00:15:25.741
Duck.

172
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:29.500
Quietly.

173
00:15:31.501 --> 00:15:32.980
I said quietly.

174
00:15:34.140 --> 00:15:35.701
That's all right.

175
00:15:39.862 --> 00:15:41.902
Would you look at this?

176
00:15:45.661 --> 00:15:46.981
Easy.

177
00:16:01.180 --> 00:16:02.743
Get down. nitwit.

178
00:16:05.022 --> 00:16:07.262
-Hey.
-Nighty-night.

179
00:16:08.982 --> 00:16:10.422
All right. let's go.

180
00:16:12.382 --> 00:16:13.342
All right!

181
00:16:14.381 --> 00:16:16.503
-You got the Laser?
-Yeah.

182
00:16:17.302 --> 00:16:21.422
-Give it to me. Come on.
-Okay. it's hot.

183
00:16:31.423 --> 00:16:33.503
-Here you go.
-Sure. here.

184
00:16:37.702 --> 00:16:39.582
Come to papa.

185
00:16:40.223 --> 00:16:43.583
-Beautiful. boss.
-look at that.

186
00:16:52.023 --> 00:16:53.303
Lt. Callahan.

187
00:16:54.983 --> 00:16:56.503
Sgt. Hightower.

188
00:16:57.983 --> 00:16:59.343
Sgt. Jones.

189
00:17:00.703 --> 00:17:01.943
Sgt. Hooks.

190
00:17:04.063 --> 00:17:05.783
Sgt. Tackleberry.

191
00:17:09.583 --> 00:17:11.064
Officer Conklin.

192
00:17:13.743 --> 00:17:17.344
-Thank you.
-All right. let's go.

193
00:17:53.824 --> 00:17:56.744
We've got some time. boys.
What say we find ourselves the bar?

194
00:17:56.824 --> 00:17:59.504
-Sure thing. boss.
-Yeah. Good idea. boss.

195
00:17:59.664 --> 00:18:00.744
Watch it. kid!

196
00:18:02.744 --> 00:18:03.943
Yeah. Nice shot.

197
00:18:05.625 --> 00:18:08.665
-They ought to keep those kids on a leash.
-Yeah.

198
00:18:13.985 --> 00:18:15.425
What an idiot.

199
00:18:24.985 --> 00:18:26.185
Boss.

200
00:18:26.785 --> 00:18:28.145
Out of the way. buddy.

201
00:18:28.224 --> 00:18:29.745
You all right?

202
00:18:30.425 --> 00:18:32.906
-How's my hair?
-Beautiful. boss.

203
00:18:32.986 --> 00:18:34.225
There he goes. boss.

204
00:18:34.306 --> 00:18:37.066
let him go.
We don't want to draw attention.

205
00:18:37.506 --> 00:18:39.146
Yeah. the diamonds.

206
00:18:39.345 --> 00:18:41.985
-Are you sure my hair's all right?
-Yeah. it looks the same.

207
00:18:42.065 --> 00:18:43.905
-How's it look?
-Hasn't budged. boss.

208
00:18:43.945 --> 00:18:45.306
All right. let's go.

209
00:18:46.786 --> 00:18:48.306
Comdt. Lassard...

210
00:18:48.385 --> 00:18:51.346
I was very sorry to learn
that we wouldn't be traveling together.

211
00:18:51.425 --> 00:18:53.305
Now. that is a disappointment.

212
00:18:54.306 --> 00:18:57.666
Lt. Proctor has booked us
on a very speciaI flight.

213
00:18:57.746 --> 00:18:59.307
VIP. Excuse me.

214
00:19:00.186 --> 00:19:04.266
VIP. I understand that you're taking
an economy flight.

215
00:19:05.346 --> 00:19:08.306
We'll just have to meet in Miami.
I'll see you there.

216
00:19:09.706 --> 00:19:11.585
-Shame.
-Morning. sir.

217
00:19:12.946 --> 00:19:15.146
Please be careful with the bag.

218
00:19:16.467 --> 00:19:18.386
Flying makes him nervous.

219
00:19:23.666 --> 00:19:25.066
Metal. please.

220
00:19:31.747 --> 00:19:33.506
Come through again. please.

221
00:19:52.227 --> 00:19:54.868
It's probably the buckle. sir.
Here. I¡¯ll get it.

222
00:19:54.948 --> 00:19:56.827
Get away from me. Proctor.

223
00:19:59.467 --> 00:20:00.747
Thank you.

224
00:20:09.508 --> 00:20:11.028
Come through. please.

225
00:20:17.547 --> 00:20:19.427
Very funny. Jones.

226
00:20:30.467 --> 00:20:31.748
Hold on. Miss?

227
00:20:32.467 --> 00:20:36.149
Could you please tell me at what gate
Flight 1545 is boarding?

228
00:20:37.189 --> 00:20:40.428
-Gate 24. sir.
-Could you aIso check and make sure...

229
00:20:40.509 --> 00:20:44.748
that I am in the speciaI VIP section?
The name is Harris.

230
00:20:46.148 --> 00:20:49.468
There is no VIP section. sir.
It's a private plane.

231
00:20:50.748 --> 00:20:52.268
A private plane.

232
00:20:52.948 --> 00:20:56.028
And you and Mr. Proctor
are the only listed passengers.

233
00:20:56.108 --> 00:20:58.948
I see. Our own plane.

234
00:20:59.509 --> 00:21:03.229
Well. Well. Harris.
You travel first-class. I must say.

235
00:21:03.270 --> 00:21:06.109
Well. it's the only way. Come. Proctor.

236
00:21:07.629 --> 00:21:10.389
-Au revoir! Bon voyage!
-Ciao!

237
00:21:10.829 --> 00:21:12.349
Auf Wiedersehen.

238
00:21:14.629 --> 00:21:15.949
Oh. my God!

239
00:21:19.669 --> 00:21:24.030
This is great! Our own airplane.
AnimaIs to play with.

240
00:21:24.230 --> 00:21:27.430
I¡¯ll tell you. this VIP treatment
is worth every penny.

241
00:21:29.710 --> 00:21:30.830
A-okay!

242
00:21:35.309 --> 00:21:38.229
Why do I put up with you?

243
00:21:40.029 --> 00:21:43.389
I think that's because
my sister married your nephew...

244
00:21:43.470 --> 00:21:45.989
-and that makes us--
-Shut up. Proctor!

245
00:21:49.030 --> 00:21:50.710
Sir. they like you!

246
00:22:00.830 --> 00:22:04.310
-Sir. what would you like to drink today?
-Nothing right now. thank you.

